A variable whose scope is restricted to a method is known as:
Which of the following are false:
possibleAnswers: a. By convention, class names begin with an uppercase letter, but methods and variables begin with a lowercase letter.
b. Instance variables can be declared anywhere inside a class.
c. Instance variables exist before methods are called on objects, while the methods are executing and after the methods complete execution.
correctAnswer: b. Instance variables can be declared anywhere inside a class.

question: Which of the following are true:

b. Most instance variable declarations are preceded with the keyword public, which is a visibility modifier.
c. Variables or methods declared with private visibility are accessible only to the methods of the class in which they are declared.

question: Which of the following statements are false:

question: Which of the following are false
